President Obama announced his intent to nominate Elisabeth Hagen as Under Secretary of Agriculture for Food Safety at the Department of Agriculture. Hagen is currently the USDA's Chief Medical Officer and has played a key role in developing and executing the agency's scientific and public health agendas. She has experience teaching and practicing medicine and holds an M.D. from Harvard Medical School.

President Obama also announced his intent to nominate Michele M. Leonhart as Administrator of Drug Enforcement at the Drug Enforcement Administration (DEA) in the Department of Justice. Leonhart has nearly 30 years of experience as a Special Agent with the DEA and has served in various management roles within the agency. She was the agency's first female Special Agent in Charge and has received numerous awards for her work. Leonhart holds a B.S. in Criminal Justice from Bemidji State University.